      "issue": "Heading used for promotional paragraph text",
      "detail": "'Please contribute to our Smart Phone and Smart Vision program – every donation will be quadrupled via matching grants from other donors! A signle donation will impact 4 lives!' is a lengthy promotional sentence (with a typo) used as an H3 heading. This is body content, not a heading."
    },
    {
      "issue": "Vague heading 'What's New'",
      "detail": "While common, this heading is vague in context because the entire page appears to be a stream of news items and updates, making it unclear what specifically falls under 'What's New' versus the many other news-like H2 headings."
    },
    {
      "issue": "No logical progression or clear content outline",
      "detail": "The heading structure does not form a coherent document outline. It mixes welcome content, news updates, success stories, donation appeals, event promotions, organizational awards, and contact information in a seemingly random order with no clear sectional grouping."
    },
    {
      "issue": "Duplicate H3 headings",
      "detail": "'See how the visually impaired benefit from your gift of a Smart Phone' appears twice as an H3, making it indistinguishable for screen reader users navigating by headings."
    },
    {
      "issue": "Sponsors heading contains instructional text",
      "detail": "'Sponsors Welcome for the VISION-AID 2023 ANNUAL EVENT . For more details, please click here' combines a section label with a call-to-action, making it unclear and overly long as a heading."
    }
  ]
}
